<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-01T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="161" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d161">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4214: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-01T16:00:00-04:00">July 1, 1931—4 p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                                <p>19. Your 25, July 1, 1 a.m. Questions raised by Greek Government
                                    are being considered. However, it will not be possible to give
                                    answers regarding these questions until the larger issues now
                                    under negotiation have been settled.<note n="8" xml:id="d161fn8">See <ref target="#pg_42">pp. 42</ref> ff.</note></p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>